(
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E196029437676FA1CFD61FA12" box="[548,675,1501,1525]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="16.[212,279,1399,1421]" captionTargetBox="[212,1172,168,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[212,1172,168,1367]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figure 9. Males of Megalopta. (A) Dorsal view of flagellum of M. guimaraesi from Formosa, Brazil; (B) ventral view of sternum 3‒4 of M. amoena from Alenquer, Brazil; (C, E) dorsal view of head; (D, F) Frontal view of head; (C) M. guarani sp. n. from Chapada dos Guimarães, Brazil; (D) M. mapinguari sp. n. from Rio Branco, Brazil; (E) M. xavante sp. n. from Nova Xavantina, Brazil; (F) M. atlantica Santos &amp; Silveira from Ipanema, Brazil. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004477" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004477/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="623">Figures 9D</figureCitation>
