<subSubSection id="62DD6540196029427486F9FDFB86FF07" lastPageId="49" lastPageNumber="624" pageId="48" pageNumber="623" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2A7836CB196029437486F9FDFE82F9B4" blockId="48.[212,1172,1596,1691]" box="[212,320,1596,1619]" pageId="48" pageNumber="623">
<heading id="713081A7196029437486F9FDFE82F9B4" box="[212,320,1596,1619]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="48" pageNumber="623" reason="5">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD9196029437486F9FDFE82F9B4" box="[212,320,1596,1619]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="623">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A7836CB196029437486F9A2FB56F97C" blockId="48.[212,1172,1596,1691]" pageId="48" pageNumber="623">
The male differs from those of 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D48196029437660F9A5FD72F99C" authority="Santos &amp; Melo, 2014" authorityName="Santos &amp; Melo" authorityYear="2014" box="[562,688,1636,1659]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="623" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guarani" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD9196029437660F9A5FD72F99C" box="[562,688,1636,1659]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="623">M. guarani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="038057A21960294376E5F9A5FD36F99C" box="[695,756,1636,1659]" pageId="48" pageNumber="623" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D4819602943777FF9A5FC78F99B" authority="Santos &amp; Melo, 2014" authorityName="Santos &amp; Melo" authorityYear="2014" box="[813,954,1636,1660]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="623" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="karitiana" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD919602943777FF9A5FC85F99C" box="[813,839,1636,1659]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="623">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="18B3EAD9196029437704F9A5FC78F99B" box="[854,954,1636,1660]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="623">karitiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="038057A2196029437790F9A5FC3CF99C" box="[962,1022,1636,1659]" pageId="48" pageNumber="623" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the shape of the medial protruding process of S4, its profile digitiform in lateral view; from 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D48196029437020F945FB56F97C" authorityName="Santos and Silveira" authorityYear="2009" box="[1138,1172,1668,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD9196029437020F945FB56F97C" box="[1138,1172,1668,1691]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="623">M.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A7836CB1961294274C2FF69FB86FF07" blockId="49.[144,1103,168,225]" pageId="49" pageNumber="624">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD91961294274C2FF69FF32FF27" box="[144,240,168,192]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="624">atlantica</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D48196129427556FF68FE5DFF27" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1879" box="[260,415,169,192]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="624" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="purpurata">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD9196129427556FF68FE5DFF27" box="[260,415,169,192]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="624">M. purpurata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D481961294275B6FF68FDAAFF27" authority="Santos &amp; Melo, 2014" authorityName="Santos &amp; Melo" authorityYear="2014" box="[484,616,169,192]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="624" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xavante" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD91961294275B6FF68FDAAFF27" box="[484,616,169,192]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="624">M. xavante</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="038057A2196129427624FF68FD7AFF27" box="[630,696,169,192]" pageId="49" pageNumber="624" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the mesosoma homogeneously metallic green and by lacking setae in the apex of medial protruding process of S4.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="62DD65401961294274C2FEE4FEABFC0C" pageId="49" pageNumber="624" type="description">
<paragraph id="2A7836CB1961294274C2FEE4FECDFEDB" blockId="49.[144,1104,293,771]" box="[144,271,293,316]" pageId="49" pageNumber="624">
<heading id="713081A71961294274C2FEE4FECDFEDB" box="[144,271,293,316]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="49" pageNumber="624" reason="5">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD91961294274C2FEE4FECDFEDB" box="[144,271,293,316]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="624">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A7836CB1961294274C2FE8DFD30FCE4" blockId="49.[144,1104,293,771]" pageId="49" pageNumber="624">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD91961294274C2FE8DFF10FE83" box="[144,210,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="624">Male.</emphasis>
(15) Scape with diameter gradually enlarging toward the apex. (16) Flagellum blackish; F1–F11 not differing in diameter; F2 about two-thirds of F 
<quantity id="ED3F9B2E19612942779CFEADFC3FFE63" box="[974,1021,364,388]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="49" pageNumber="624" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
length (
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E1961294274CAFE4DFECCFE43" box="[152,270,396,420]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="16.[212,279,1399,1421]" captionTargetBox="[212,1172,168,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[212,1172,168,1367]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figure 9. Males of Megalopta. (A) Dorsal view of flagellum of M. guimaraesi from Formosa, Brazil; (B) ventral view of sternum 3‒4 of M. amoena from Alenquer, Brazil; (C, E) dorsal view of head; (D, F) Frontal view of head; (C) M. guarani sp. n. from Chapada dos Guimarães, Brazil; (D) M. mapinguari sp. n. from Rio Branco, Brazil; (E) M. xavante sp. n. from Nova Xavantina, Brazil; (F) M. atlantica Santos &amp; Silveira from Ipanema, Brazil. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004477" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004477/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="624">Figure 9D</figureCitation>
); F6–F11, in anterior view, with the anterior and posterior margins flat, in posterior view with basal glabrous area at same level of remaining surface. (17) Metanotum with integument, in dorsal view, not hidden by short plumose pillosity (
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E1961294274CAFE2DFED5FDE3" box="[152,279,492,516]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="19.[144,213,1405,1427]" captionTargetBox="[144,1104,168,1365]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[144,1104,168,1373]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 11. Males of Megalopta. (A, C, D). Posterolateral view of mesosoma; (A) M. karitiana sp. n. from Ouro Preto do Oeste, Brazil; (B) ventral view of sternum 3‒4 of M. mapinguari sp. n. from Rio Branco, Brazil; (C) M. mapinguari sp. n. from Rio Branco, Brazil; (D) M. xavante sp. n. from Nova Xavantina, Brazil; (E) dorsal view of mesosoma of M. atlantica Santos &amp; Silveira from Ipanema, Brazil; (F) posterior view of mesosoma of M. purpurata Smith (holotype) from Tefé, Brazil. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004481/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="624">Figure 11C</figureCitation>
). (18) Basal area of metapostnotum metallic green, its length 0.5× that of metanotum, longitudinal rugulosities present in the mid portion (
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E1961294277D5FDCAFBCBFDC4" box="[903,1033,523,547]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="19.[144,213,1405,1427]" captionTargetBox="[144,1104,168,1365]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[144,1104,168,1373]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 11. Males of Megalopta. (A, C, D). Posterolateral view of mesosoma; (A) M. karitiana sp. n. from Ouro Preto do Oeste, Brazil; (B) ventral view of sternum 3‒4 of M. mapinguari sp. n. from Rio Branco, Brazil; (C) M. mapinguari sp. n. from Rio Branco, Brazil; (D) M. xavante sp. n. from Nova Xavantina, Brazil; (E) dorsal view of mesosoma of M. atlantica Santos &amp; Silveira from Ipanema, Brazil; (F) posterior view of mesosoma of M. purpurata Smith (holotype) from Tefé, Brazil. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004481/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="624">Figure 11C</figureCitation>
). (19) Metepisternum with sparse pilosity, integument visible through pilosity; posterior upper margin of metepisternum unmodified, lacking a velvety process. (20) 1st and 2nd tarsomeres of foreleg with longest simple setae shorter than the summed length of the three apical tarsomeres. (21) S3 with longitudinal sulcus, posterolateral margin notched (
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E1961294274ADFD6AFE40FD24" box="[255,386,683,707]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="19.[144,213,1405,1427]" captionTargetBox="[144,1104,168,1365]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[144,1104,168,1373]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 11. Males of Megalopta. (A, C, D). Posterolateral view of mesosoma; (A) M. karitiana sp. n. from Ouro Preto do Oeste, Brazil; (B) ventral view of sternum 3‒4 of M. mapinguari sp. n. from Rio Branco, Brazil; (C) M. mapinguari sp. n. from Rio Branco, Brazil; (D) M. xavante sp. n. from Nova Xavantina, Brazil; (E) dorsal view of mesosoma of M. atlantica Santos &amp; Silveira from Ipanema, Brazil; (F) posterior view of mesosoma of M. purpurata Smith (holotype) from Tefé, Brazil. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004481/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="624">Figure 11B</figureCitation>
). (22) S4 with medial protruding process, profile of process digitiform in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E1961294275EBFD0AFDFAFD04" box="[441,568,715,739]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="19.[144,213,1405,1427]" captionTargetBox="[144,1104,168,1365]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[144,1104,168,1373]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 11. Males of Megalopta. (A, C, D). Posterolateral view of mesosoma; (A) M. karitiana sp. n. from Ouro Preto do Oeste, Brazil; (B) ventral view of sternum 3‒4 of M. mapinguari sp. n. from Rio Branco, Brazil; (C) M. mapinguari sp. n. from Rio Branco, Brazil; (D) M. xavante sp. n. from Nova Xavantina, Brazil; (E) dorsal view of mesosoma of M. atlantica Santos &amp; Silveira from Ipanema, Brazil; (F) posterior view of mesosoma of M. purpurata Smith (holotype) from Tefé, Brazil. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004481/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="624">Figure 11B</figureCitation>
); basal portion glabrous; posterolateral margin notched, notch not extending to basal half of sclerite.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A7836CB1961294274C2FC89FEF2FCB8" blockId="49.[144,1103,840,935]" box="[144,304,840,863]" pageId="49" pageNumber="624">
<heading id="713081A71961294274C2FC89FEF2FCB8" box="[144,304,840,863]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="49" pageNumber="624" reason="5">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD91961294274C2FC89FEF2FCB8" box="[144,304,840,863]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="624">Measurements</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A7836CB1961294274C2FCAEFD76FC40" blockId="49.[144,1103,840,935]" pageId="49" pageNumber="624">Approximate body length: (12.4); intertegular distance: (3.8); maximum width of head: (2.9); length of forewing with tegula: (10).</paragraph>
