<paragraph id="2A7836CB1961294274C2F982FE39F97C" blockId="49.[144,1104,1564,1691]" pageId="49" pageNumber="624">The specific epithet honours the ‘Mapinguari’, used here as a noun in apposition. The ‘Mapinguari’, a Brazilian folklore character, is popularly known as a monster that lives in the Amazon Rainforest.</paragraph>
